<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3524&amp;p=26542#p26542</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3524&amp;p=26542#p26542"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mandelbrot / Fractals in 6502?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3524&amp;p=26542#p26542"><![CDATA[
The Mandelbrot and Julia sets use the same formula, but they use C differently.<br /><br />The Mandelbrot set use the current complex number (where the pixel coordinates are) for the value of C on every iteration, thus it changes on every pixel.<br /><br />Julia sets use one fixed complex number for the value of C on every iteration, thus it remains fixed.  The fixed complex number is supposed to be assigned before rendering the Julia set.<br /><br />Since Julia sets use a fixed point and the Mandelbrot set uses every point, it can be said that the Mandelbrot set is an index to every possible Julia set.  I will even go so far as to say the Mandelbrot set *is* every Julia set mashed up together in one fractal universe.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=119">doppelganger</a> — Mon Aug 27, 2007 7:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
