<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3524&amp;p=26541#p26541"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mandelbrot / Fractals in 6502?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=3524&amp;p=26541#p26541"><![CDATA[
Julia sets and Mandelbrot sets are calculated with the same recurrence relation<br /><br />z[n+1] = z[n]^2 + c<br /><br />For the Mandlebrot set, z[0] = 0 and c varies over the entire complex plane.<br /><br />For Julia sets, a specific complex value c is selected, and z[0] varies over the entire complex plane.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=190">kingshriek</a> — Mon Aug 27, 2007 7:15 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
